{
  "texts": [
    "This initial score, S(C 0), is the baseline for comparison in subsequent iterations.",
    "At each iteration i, the current best-known output, O C i, is evaluated, and a set of hypotheses,",
    "If the new score S i+1 is greater than the best-known score S best = max(S i+1, S best), the new variant is considered superior, and the best-known variant is updated as follows.",
    "The process continues iteratively until a stopping condition is met, either when the improvement between iterations becomes smaller than a predefined threshold |S i+1 -S best | < ϵ, or when a maximum number of iterations is reached.",
    "Upon termination, the proposed method returns the best-known variant C best and its output O best."
  ]
}